Citations
Date: 15/8/1983
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 11
Edition:
Quote: Catch - a huntaway moving from one side of a mob to the other to change the direction of the sheep. On a zig-zag course, sheep that have been on a slew to the right may need a strong catch on the right to move them directly to the left slew.
